    <div class="section-title">
      <h2>About Little Worlds Workshop</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="about-text">
    <p>
      In the middle of our everyday full and busy lives, it can feel hard to engage with your child in a focused meaningful way.  We want to give them all of our attention while they tell us stories or want to play, but our attention is so often pulled in a myriad of necessary directions.
    </p><p>
      Little Worlds workshop is here to help! Our classes are designed to create the space and time for you and child to connect through play and creative activities and create positive relational habits that you can carry forward into your everyday life. The classes are designed for pairs of one child (aged 4-6) and one parent. You and your child will create a little world inside a sand tray and then capture the story of that world in a book and a terrarium you will be able to take home. Elements of storytelling, photography, mindfulness, and relaxation skills will be woven throughout the workshop. Every parent/child set has their own teepee to cuddle up in or play.
    </p><p>
      Throughout the three week workshop, you will be given the opportunity to follow your child’s lead through play and get a glimpse of the little world inside his/her head. This is a time and space to simply enjoy the unique person that is your child. This is a no pressure environment! The emphasis of the class is on providing a positive space for you and your child to smile together and not on producing a “perfect” product.
    </p><p>
      We spend a lot of our time with our kids in this age range, shuttling them from one activity to another. Little Worlds is designed specifically to allow you to engage in activities with and focused on you and your child. It is a safe, fun, and creative environment designed to allow you to do the thing you want the most, be 100% present with your kid.  It is not a therapy group. It is like an art or play class with a very important added bonus.
    </p>
