  <div id="expect">
    <div class="section-title">
      <h2>What To Expect</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="about-text">
      <p>
        Expect to engage with and enjoy the unique person who is your child,
        first and foremost! You and your child will have your own teepee to start
        off in and return to whenever you would like. There will be a simple relaxation
        exercise and then you and your child will have the opportunity to
        explore and create in a sand tray with a variety of toys and props.
        We will end with more teepee time, a snack, and another chance to relax our bodies and brains.
        The second workshop will include some play with an instant camera and photo book and we will all make our
         own little world terrariums during the third session.
      </p><p>
        I know at times it can feel hard to parent our children while around other parents and children. The workshop is designed to be a safe place in every sense of the word. This is a special time where there will not be as many rules or expectations, for us or our children, as there may be elsewhere. There is no “wrong” way to experience this workshop, the only goal is for you and your child to connect. There are options for other activities if your child isn’t feeling one of the activities. You can stay in the teepee the whole time if that is what your child needs. The space is designed to be used by children. I am well aware of how children can use a space. Please do not be worried that your children will break or ruin something. The sole purpose of these workshops is to help you and your child disconnect from the everyday worries and reconnect with each other.
      </p>
